	(115, 12, '08:00', 'Registration and Safety Briefing', 'Check-in, hazard review, and exercise rules.', 115, 1, '2026-07-13 05:40:04', '2026-07-13 05:40:04'),
	(116, 12, '08:15', 'Skills Station Rotation', 'Hands-on Multi-Hazard response practice.', 116, 2, '2026-07-13 05:40:04', '2026-07-13 05:40:04'),
	(117, 12, '09:30', 'Scenario Activation', 'Timed scenario with role-based tasks.', 117, 3, '2026-07-13 05:40:04', '2026-07-13 05:40:04'),
	(118, 12, '10:30', 'Evacuation or Recovery Phase', 'Movement to assembly area and status reporting.', 118, 4, '2026-07-13 05:40:04', '2026-07-13 05:40:04'),
	(119, 12, '11:15', 'Debrief and Evaluation', 'After-action review and lessons learned.', 119, 5, '2026-07-13 05:40:04', '2026-07-13 05:40:04'),
	(120, 2, '08:05', 'Registration, Orientation & Safety Briefing', 'Participants register, receive an overview of the exercise objectives, schedule, and critical safety protocols, including emergency exits and first aid points. Emphasize the \'Stop, Drop, and Roll\' principle if clothing catches fire and the importance of not attempting to fight large fires.', 7, 1, '2026-07-13 05:48:20', '2026-07-13 05:48:20'),
	(121, 2, '08:25', 'Introduction to Fire Safety and Extinguishers', 'A theoretical session covering the basics of fire (fire triangle), different classes of fire (A, B, C, D, K), types of fire extinguishers, and the \'PASS\' method (Pull, Aim, Squeeze, Sweep) for effective operation. Discussion on when to fight a fire versus when to evacuate.', 8, 2, '2026-07-13 05:48:20', '2026-07-13 05:48:20'),
	(122, 2, '08:55', 'Live Demonstration of Fire Extinguisher Use', 'The Lead Trainer demonstrates the proper handling and operation of a fire extinguisher on a controlled, simulated fire (e.g., fire pan). Emphasis on safety distance, aiming at the base of the fire, and sweeping motion.', 9, 3, '2026-07-13 05:48:20', '2026-07-13 05:48:20'),
	(123, 2, '09:20', 'Hands-on Practice: Dry Run (PASS Method)', 'Participants practice the \'PASS\' method using discharged or training fire extinguishers without live fire. This activity focuses on muscle memory for pulling the pin, aiming, squeezing the handle, and sweeping motion. Trainers provide immediate feedback.', 10, 4, '2026-07-13 05:48:20', '2026-07-13 05:48:20'),
	(124, 2, '10:00', 'Simulated Fire Extinguishment Drill', 'Under strict supervision, participants take turns extinguishing a small, controlled fire (e.g., in a fire pan or designated burn area) using a live fire extinguisher. This activity tests their practical application of the \'PASS\' method in a realistic scenario.', 11, 5, '2026-07-13 05:48:20', '2026-07-13 05:48:20'),
	(125, 2, '10:40', 'Debriefing, Q&A, and Feedback', 'A facilitated discussion reviewing the exercise, addressing participant questions, clarifying misconceptions, and gathering feedback. Trainers provide constructive criticism and reinforce key learning points. Certificates of participation may be distributed.', 12, 6, '2026-07-13 05:48:20', '2026-07-13 05:48:20'),
	(126, 13, '08:15', 'Orientation, Registration, and Safety Briefing', 'Welcome participants, provide an overview of the exercise objectives and schedule, and conduct a comprehensive safety briefing covering emergency procedures and ground rules for the simulation.', 120, 1, '2026-07-13 05:50:02', '2026-07-13 05:50:02'),
	(127, 13, '08:30', 'Lecture-Demonstration: Fire Safety Basics and PASS Method', 'A theoretical session covering common causes of fires, types of fire extinguishers (Class A, B, C, D, K), and a detailed demonstration of the \'PASS\' (Pull, Aim, Squeeze, Sweep) method for operating a fire extinguisher.', 121, 2, '2026-07-13 05:50:02', '2026-07-13 05:50:02'),
	(128, 13, '09:00', 'Hands-on Practice: Fire Extinguisher Operation', 'Participants will individually practice the \'PASS\' method using training fire extinguishers on a controlled, simulated fire (e.g., a fire pan with controlled fuel or a water-based fire simulator). Emphasis on proper stance and technique.', 122, 3, '2026-07-13 05:50:02', '2026-07-13 05:50:02'),
	(129, 13, '09:40', 'Scenario Simulation: Responding to a Small Fire Incident', 'A controlled functional exercise where participants respond to a simulated small electrical fire in a designated area. Participants will assess the situation, decide on appropriate action, and apply the fire extinguisher as practiced.', 123, 4, '2026-07-13 05:50:02', '2026-07-13 05:50:02'),
	(130, 13, '10:05', 'Debriefing and Open Forum', 'A facilitated discussion to review the exercise, gather feedback from participants, discuss lessons learned, identify strengths and areas for improvement in fire response.', 124, 5, '2026-07-13 05:50:02', '2026-07-13 05:50:02'),
	(131, 13, '10:13', 'Wrap-up and Closing Remarks', 'Summary of key takeaways, acknowledgment of participants and personnel, and final announcements.', 125, 6, '2026-07-13 05:50:02', '2026-07-13 05:50:02');
